" The NAACP Travel Advisory for the State of Missouri , which is scheduled to take effect until August 28 , 2017 , urges African-American travelers , visitors and Missourians to pay special attention and exercise extreme caution when traveling through the state , as a number of questionable , race-based incidents have recently occurred and are recorded throughout the state , " the group 's statement said .
A recent Missouri law making it harder for people to win discrimination lawsuits , as well as the state 's law enforcement agencies disproportionately targeting minorities , prompted the group to issue the travel warning , the NAACP said .
" They have civil rights violations that happen to people .
They are stopped because of their skin color , they are beaten up or killed , " the president of the Missouri NAACP , Rod Chapel , told the Kansas City Star .
