The stelae with the individual planets - including Pluto , which has been reduced to a dwarf planet at the end point - are positioned exactly at a distance and scale of one to two billion .
The earth thus shrinks to a sphere of 6.5 millimetres in diameter , while the sun , which stands exactly 75 metres away , measures 70 centimetres .
The total distance of the planetary path is about four kilometers .
While the light from the sun to the Pluto takes about eight hours , pedestrians need a good hour to reach the stele with Pluto .
Pedestrians are therefore faster than the light in space .
