Roll backwards : the city is hiring 46 kitchen assistants
The city organises the kite lunch table itself again .
With fixed contact persons for the children and an assignment to the team .
In urban nurseries , the clock is turned back .
On 1 September , the city of Krefeld will take over the food supply in the municipal daycare centres ( Kitas ) again on its own .
For Sonja Pommeranz , deputy head of the Youth Aid department , this is good news : " we were all very pleased . "
Cooking continues outside the house : a caterer takes on this task and delivers freshly cooked chilled food .
In the Krefeld region , the city runs 46 day-care centres , while in 44 children receive a warm meal at lunchtime .
In the past year of kitesurfing , 2800 children sat at the tables , and the demand is growing steadily .
" In the meantime , it 's not just children who are cared for 45 hours a week who eat lunch at the Kita , " explains Pommeranz .
" The offer also applies to 35-hour care if children stay until 2pm . "
From 1 September , 46 part-time workers will be in charge of the kitchen : they will warm up the food supplied , supplement it with salad , raw food and fruit , individually portioning the meal , handing out the food , clearing it , rinsing and cleaning the kitchen .
" The employees are permanently assigned to a nursery , " says Pommeranz .
The size - there are two-group as well as seven-group facilities - determines the number of hours .
" The kitchen assistants are now firmly part of the kitesurfing team , " says Pommeranz satisfied .
" So they are much more involved and it is easier for the management to implement pedagogical concepts . "
Because that 's also what it 's all about : healthy eating and cooking classes .
" The children should help prepare the food . "
The direct connection of kitchen power to the team makes sense .
For the children , too .
" They have a known force in the Kita , a person familiar to them , and not constantly changing people . "
This continuity is important for the children .
The cleaning of the kita-rooms - previously also the task of the kitchen staff - will in future be done by special cleaning staff .
This option - the separation of cleaning and kitchen service - has , in addition to improving the quality of the kitchen service , the charm that it has turned out to be the most economical in the cost comparison between owning and contracting out for the city , according to the Press Office .
This is despite the fact that 46 part-time workers are being recruited .
" But with around 750 people in the field of education , these hours do not weigh as much , " says Sonja Pommeranz .
